<p>'Oh my goodness, that's amazing! Does it look smudgy though?' one asked, to which Nancy replied: 'No - wipe it on with the finger and off with a cloth. Try it.' </p>

<p>Last month the 2014 Bake Off winner shared an eco-friendly way to shift grass and food stains from clothing in as little as two hours.</p>

<p>Taking to Instagram, Nancy showed off her 'genius' cleaning hack - which simply requires cold water and distilled white vinegar - in a series of short videos.</p>
